#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.3:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Bālavagga "
msgstr "1. Fools "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Cintīsutta "
msgstr "3. Thinking "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an3.3:1.1"
msgid "“Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, bālassa bālalakkhaṇāni bālanimittāni bālāpadānāni. "
msgstr "“There are these three characteristics, signs, and manifestations of a fool. "

msgctxt "an3.3:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.3:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bālo duccintitacintī ca hoti dubbhāsitabhāsī ca dukkaṭakammakārī ca. "
msgstr "A fool thinks poorly, speaks poorly, and acts poorly. "

#. VAR: cedaṃ → no cetaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
#. VAR: kena naṃ paṇḍitā jāneyyuṃ → tena naṃ paṇḍitā na jāneyyuṃ (mr) | na naṃ paṇḍitā jāneyyuṃ (?)
msgctxt "an3.3:1.4"
msgid "No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, bālo duccintitacintī ca abhavissa dubbhāsitabhāsī ca dukkaṭakammakārī ca, kena naṃ paṇḍitā jāneyyuṃ: "
msgstr "If a fool didn’t think poorly, speak poorly, and act poorly, then how would the astute know of them: "

msgctxt "an3.3:1.5"
msgid "‘bālo ayaṃ bhavaṃ asappuriso’ti? "
msgstr "‘This fellow is a fool, a bad person’? "

msgctxt "an3.3:1.6"
msgid "Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, bālo duccintitacintī ca hoti dubbhāsitabhāsī ca dukkaṭakammakārī ca tasmā naṃ paṇḍitā jānanti: "
msgstr "But since a fool does think poorly, speak poorly, and act poorly, then the astute do know of them: "

msgctxt "an3.3:1.7"
msgid "‘bālo ayaṃ bhavaṃ asappuriso’ti. "
msgstr "‘This fellow is a fool, a bad person’. "

msgctxt "an3.3:1.8"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi bālassa bālalakkhaṇāni bālanimittāni bālāpadānāni. "
msgstr "These are the three characteristics, signs, and manifestations of a fool. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.103, sc2
msgctxt "an3.3:2.1"
msgid "Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, paṇḍitassa paṇḍitalakkhaṇāni paṇḍitanimittāni paṇḍitāpadānāni. "
msgstr "There are these three characteristics, signs, and manifestations of an astute person. "

msgctxt "an3.3:2.2"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.3:2.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, paṇḍito sucintitacintī ca hoti subhāsitabhāsī ca sukatakammakārī ca. "
msgstr "An astute person thinks well, speaks well, and acts well. "

msgctxt "an3.3:2.4"
msgid "No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, paṇḍito sucintitacintī ca abhavissa subhāsitabhāsī ca sukatakammakārī ca, kena naṃ paṇḍitā jāneyyuṃ: "
msgstr "If an astute person didn’t think well, speak well, and act well, then how would the astute know of them: "

msgctxt "an3.3:2.5"
msgid "‘paṇḍito ayaṃ bhavaṃ sappuriso’ti? "
msgstr "‘This fellow is astute, a good person’? "

msgctxt "an3.3:2.6"
msgid "Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, paṇḍito sucintitacintī ca hoti subhāsitabhāsī ca sukatakammakārī ca tasmā naṃ paṇḍitā jānanti: "
msgstr "But since an astute person does think well, speak well, and act well, then the astute do know of them: "

msgctxt "an3.3:2.7"
msgid "‘paṇḍito ayaṃ bhavaṃ sappuriso’ti. "
msgstr "‘This fellow is astute, a good person’. "

msgctxt "an3.3:2.8"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi paṇḍitassa paṇḍitalakkhaṇāni paṇḍitanimittāni paṇḍitāpadānāni. "
msgstr "These are the three characteristics, signs, and manifestations of an astute person. "

msgctxt "an3.3:2.9"
msgid "Tasmātiha … pe …. "
msgstr "So you should train …” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.3:2.10"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

